The second round of the presidential election kicked off in France on Sunday.

Just like five years ago, voters are choosing between current President Emmanuel Macron and Marine Le Pen, the former longtime leader of the right-wing National Rally party, in a runoff.

In the first round on April 10, Macron won 27.85% of the vote. Le Pen came in second with 23.15%.

Left-wing politician Jean-Luc Melenchon, who won 21.95% and came in third, urged his supporters not to vote for Le Pen, but refused to endorse Macron. Eric Zemmour, a far-right candidate and political newcomer who came in fourth with 7.07%, endorsed Le Pen.

Macron won the race, but overall this is a huge win. Better that I could have imagined. I was honestly not expecting this.

The race was 58.2 for Macron to 41.8% for Marine Le Pen. It might seem like a blowout, but it's getting closer. Here's a bit of French history.

The Le Pen's have run for president every year since 1974 except one. They made it to the second round in 2002, 2017, and 2022.

1974: 0.75%
1981: Did not run
1988: 14.39%
1995: 15%
2002: 16.86%
2007: 10.44%
2012: 17.9%
2017: 21%
2022: 23%

2002 was remarkable. It was the first time that a "Far right" party in France had made it to the second round since their 5th Republic was founded, in 1958. What happened? The whole country united against them. They only got 17.8% in the second round. 1% more than they got the first round.

After 2007, the senior Le Pen stopped running and his daughter took over.

In 2012 she did better than he did, but not enough to go the second round. In 2017 she was able to get the second round and not have the entire country unite against her. She still only got 1/3 of the vote. It was 33.9%-66.1% and after Le Pen advanced to the second round in 2022, I thought the results would be similar to 2017. She increased by nearly 8 percentage points. She's now very serious as the true opposition.

What's even more remarkable, is that there was a Saboteur in the first round. A second far right candidate named Eric Zamour who was Jewish and Algerian and he ran to try to stop her from advancing to the second round because she stood a chance at winning.

Things are chancing in France and everywhere else. What will happen in 2027?

23 Apr 2022
Trump Reveals Trailer of Explosive ‚Äò2000 Mules‚Äô Ballot Harvesting Documentary at Ohio Rally

LISTEN TO ARTICLE___________________3:59

Former President Donald Trump on Saturday evening played the trailer of the forthcoming explosive documentary ‚Äú2000 Mules‚Äù which reveals a wide scale ballot trafficking network of ballot harvesters across several swing states. Trump played the trailer at the rally where he is campaigning with J.D. Vance, the candidate he endorsed for U.S. Senate in this year‚Äôs Ohio GOP Senate primary.

The documentary, the product of a years-long investigation by election integrity group True The Vote and produced by conservative filmmaker Dinesh D‚ÄôSouza, has been long-awaited and is chock full of surveillance footage showing specific instances of people taking multiple ballots to drop boxes and making trips to several boxes around their states. The investigation has been anticipated since Breitbart News first revealed it last summer, and Trump has been hyping it for some time now in statements and commentary.

WATCH:
The trailer opens with a panel of Salem Radio Network hosts split on what happened in the 2020 election. Salem Media Group worked with D‚ÄôSouza and True The Vote on the film, and the panel‚Äîwhich includes Turning Point USA‚Äôs Charlie Kirk and radio hosts Dennis Prager, Larry Elder, Eric Metaxas, and Dr. Sebastian Gorka‚Äîopens with them discussing how they, before viewing this evidence, were not sure what exactly happened in the 2020 election and were awaiting more evidence.

Then the film cuts to True The Vote‚Äôs Catherine Engelbrecht who tells D‚ÄôSouza, ‚ÄúWe have been working on something big.‚Äù
‚ÄúI‚Äôve been working with Gregg Phillips,‚Äù Engelbrecht says. ‚ÄúHe has a deep background in election intelligence.‚Äù

On screen, voters see Engelbrecht and Phillips breaking down the data and information that they have collected. ‚ÄúTrue The Vote has the largest store of election intelligence for the 2020 elections in the world,‚Äù Phillips says. ‚ÄúNo one has more data than we do.‚Äù

On-screen graphics tell viewers that True The Vote used cell phone GPS geo tracking data across the battleground states.

‚ÄúWe identified in Atlanta 242 mules that went to an average of 24 drop boxes,‚Äù Phillips says. ‚ÄúIn Philadelphia alone, we‚Äôve identified more than 1,100 mules.‚Äù

When D‚ÄôSouza asked Engelbrecht to define a ‚Äúmule,‚Äù she replies by saying they are a ‚Äúperson picking up ballots and running them to the drop boxes.‚Äù

‚ÄúThis is not grandma out walking her dog,‚Äù Phillips says. ‚ÄúBad backgrounds, bad reputations. They are interested in one thing: That‚Äôs money.‚Äù

‚ÄúIn no shape, in no way, in no time is that legal,‚Äù Engelbrecht adds.

‚ÄúThis is organized crime,‚Äù Phillips says.
